### Default LHAPDF choices => EwkPDFWeightProducer takes too long
### in CMSSW versions less or equal than CMSSW_3_1_2
###
### To save time (by orders of magnitude), you should install the 
### "full" LHAPDF package on your machine under $CMSSW_BASE/external/$SCRAM_ARCH/. 
### If your CMSSW version is associated to LHAPDF 5.6.0 (5.7.0) packages 
### (check the $LHAPATH variable), then you may alternatively get the LHAPDF structure
### from LHAPDF_PREFIX=/afs/cern.ch/user/j/jalcaraz/public/lhapdf-5.6.0
### (or LHAPDF_PREFIX=/afs/cern.ch/user/j/jalcaraz/public/lhapdf-5.7.0). 
###
### Proceed as follows (assuming that you have access to AFS CERN):
###    1) mkdir -p $CMSSW_BASE/lib/$SCRAM_ARCH/
###    2) cp -RP $LHAPDF_PREFIX/lib/libLHAPDF* $CMSSW_BASE/lib/$SCRAM_ARCH/
###    3) scramv1 b; ...
###
### IMPORTANT: DO NOT DO "scramv1 b distclean" AFTER THE PREVIOUS OPERATION:
###            A cleanup will remove the whole $CMSSW_BASE/lib/$SCRAM_ARCH/ 
###            directory, forcing you to redo 1) and 2) again.

<use name=LHAPDF>
<export>
      <lib name=ElectroWeakAnalysisUtilities>
</export>

